{
  "stem": "4361.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Hitler awarded 2/5 of Transylvania to Hungary, who became Hitler's ally, and gave nothing to Romania as punishment for Romania not joining the Axis.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, Sighet became Hungary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I think the tragedy of the not only Hungarian Jews but the tragedy of the Transylvanian Jews began.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father, who grew up during the Austro-Hungarian regime, was always at heart a Hungarian patriot.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember him telling me that when he was in school, every-- for several years while he was in high school came March 15, which was one of the great Hungarian holidays, something like 4th of July.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was the one who would recite a very famous poem by the great national poet Petofi, Andrej Petofi, Andre.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- the poem was [HUNGARIAN].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, I didn't learn the poem, but I remember my father telling me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hungarians, stand up.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Get up.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Join.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The homeland is calling you and, you know, exhorting the person to be patriotic and stand up for what's right and for the Hungarian homeland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so my father was truly a Hungarian patriot.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when the occupation occurred and the day before, the Hungarian contingent army was supposed to occupy Sighet, which was early September.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The night before-- 1940.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The night before-- because the award was done in August, end of August.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it took a little time to, to, to get the logistics about occupation.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Romanians had to withdraw, and then the Hungarians came into my town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The night before and the day before, my father bedecked the town, the main street, with silk flags that he had little seamstresses sew throughout the night.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He gave the silk, red, green, and white.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
